WEBVTT

00:02.635 --> 00:04.237
<i>[FUNK BEAT PLAYING]</i>

00:04.270 --> 00:08.074
[SPORTS ANNOUNCER SPEAKING
INDISTINCTLY OVER TV]

00:08.108 --> 00:09.342
Chris,
look at your sister.

00:09.376 --> 00:10.410
What happened to her?

00:10.443 --> 00:11.745
You weren't watching her,

00:11.778 --> 00:13.213
that's what happened to her.

00:13.246 --> 00:15.281
I told you I wanted a cookie.

00:15.315 --> 00:17.217
Mom, I just sat down
for a minute.

00:17.250 --> 00:19.319
Do you know
what can happen in a minute?

00:22.322 --> 00:24.724
Now, go get your sister
washed up now.

00:24.758 --> 00:27.093
[SPORTS ANNOUNCER CONTINUES
INDISTINCTLY]

00:27.127 --> 00:28.428
Come on, Tonya.

00:28.461 --> 00:30.163
NARRATOR:
<i>Thanks to Drew and Tonya,</i>

00:30.196 --> 00:31.498
<i>I was taking care of kids</i>

00:31.531 --> 00:33.400
<i>until I was taking care</i>
<i>of my own kids.</i>

00:33.433 --> 00:35.135
Chris, get me
some potato chips.

00:35.168 --> 00:36.670
Chris, help me
with my homework.

00:36.703 --> 00:38.138
Chris, find
my doll.

00:38.171 --> 00:39.572
Make me a peanut butter
and jelly sandwich.

00:39.606 --> 00:41.408
Make me Kool-Aid.
Strap up my shoe.

00:41.441 --> 00:43.176
Chris, I'm going
to take a shower.

00:43.209 --> 00:44.177
Watch the kids.

00:44.210 --> 00:46.179
Chris, tie my shoe!

00:46.212 --> 00:48.114
Chris, I'm going
to pick up my Porgy's.

00:48.148 --> 00:49.315
Watch the kids!

00:49.349 --> 00:51.518
Chris, help!
My head is stuck!

00:51.551 --> 00:53.586
Chris, I'm going to eat
some peanuts.

00:53.620 --> 00:54.654
Watch the kids.

00:54.688 --> 00:57.123
I'm going to get
my mustache waxed.

00:57.157 --> 00:58.625
Watch the kids.

00:58.658 --> 00:59.693
Chris!
Chris!

00:59.726 --> 01:01.628
Chris!
Chris!

01:01.661 --> 01:02.729
Chris!
Chris!

01:02.762 --> 01:05.098
[***]

01:10.537 --> 01:13.139
<i>* Aww, make it funky now </i>

01:36.296 --> 01:38.832
[SPORTS ANNOUNCER SPEAKING
INDISTINCTLY OVER TV]

01:38.865 --> 01:40.667
Whoa!
Whoa!

01:40.700 --> 01:43.203
NARRATOR:
<i>The one thing that</i>
<i>Drew and I did together</i>

01:43.236 --> 01:45.672
<i>was watch basketball games</i>
<i>and</i>Rocky<i>movies.</i>

01:45.705 --> 01:47.607
<i>Tonight was basketball.</i>

01:47.640 --> 01:49.876
Whoa! See that shot?
Whoa!

01:49.909 --> 01:53.446
NARRATOR:
<i>But since we only had one TV,</i>
<i>we had to share with Tonya,</i>

01:53.480 --> 01:55.482
<i>and Tonya always got her way.</i>

01:55.515 --> 01:58.218
Mama said I can watch
<i>Three's Company.</i>

01:58.251 --> 02:00.286
We're watching the game.
I don't care.

02:02.288 --> 02:03.757
[REMOTE CONTROL CLICKS]
<i>[***]</i>

02:03.790 --> 02:04.724
Move.

02:08.461 --> 02:10.530
<i>* Ooh, so you say </i>

02:10.563 --> 02:11.865
Mm.

02:11.898 --> 02:13.933
Oh, hey, baby.

02:13.967 --> 02:15.201
How was work?

02:15.235 --> 02:16.336
Hard.

02:17.804 --> 02:19.205
You know,
I was thinking

02:19.239 --> 02:22.275
that maybe we should go out,
you know?

02:22.308 --> 02:24.244
Have dinner...

02:24.277 --> 02:26.212
relax a little.

02:26.246 --> 02:27.547
Why would I go out to relax,

02:27.580 --> 02:29.649
when I can relax at home
for free?

02:29.683 --> 02:32.519
NARRATOR:
<i>That was my father's</i>
<i>rationale for everything.</i>

02:32.552 --> 02:34.654
Twenty dollars
to get in the club?

02:34.688 --> 02:37.357
We can dance at home
for free.

02:37.390 --> 02:39.526
I just wanted to
do something nice.

02:39.559 --> 02:40.794
That's all.

02:40.827 --> 02:42.462
I think staying home
is nice.

02:42.495 --> 02:43.963
Well, you're not here
all day.

02:43.997 --> 02:45.432
Well, why don't I
stay home,

02:45.465 --> 02:47.334
and you can go out
and work two jobs?

02:47.367 --> 02:49.703
[SPEAKING IN MUFFLED
SLOW-MOTION]
I'm sorry.

02:49.736 --> 02:52.939
NARRATOR:
<i>Where's a time machine</i>
<i>where you could just go back</i>

02:52.972 --> 02:54.507
<i>and shut up?</i>

02:54.541 --> 02:56.509
I did not mean-- I'm not
trying to take anything away

02:56.543 --> 02:58.311
from what you do here.
That's okay.

02:58.345 --> 03:00.246
If you don't want to go out,
you don't have to.

03:00.280 --> 03:01.548
No, look--
It's okay, no.

03:01.581 --> 03:02.716
Enough said.

03:02.749 --> 03:05.685
It's over. Over.

03:05.719 --> 03:08.688
NARRATOR:
<i>There are two things</i>
<i>my father knew for sure:</i>

03:08.722 --> 03:10.557
<i>He knew he knew nothing</i>
<i>for sure,</i>

03:10.590 --> 03:12.425
<i>and he knew</i>
<i>this wasn't over.</i>

03:12.459 --> 03:14.561
[***]

03:17.597 --> 03:18.898
KIDS:
Hey, Dad.

03:18.932 --> 03:20.533
Hey, guys.

03:20.567 --> 03:22.302
Y'all eating already?

03:22.335 --> 03:23.470
KIDS:
Mm-hmm.

03:24.504 --> 03:25.572
Where's your mother?

03:25.605 --> 03:27.007
KIDS:
In the kitchen.

03:30.777 --> 03:32.278
Hey, babe.

03:33.046 --> 03:34.447
What's for dinner?

03:34.481 --> 03:36.349
Well, the kids
are having chicken.

03:36.383 --> 03:38.284
What about me?

03:38.318 --> 03:39.486
Well, you got two jobs.

03:39.519 --> 03:40.987
You could take
your two-job money

03:41.021 --> 03:42.655
and go buy you
a two-job meal.

03:46.359 --> 03:47.761
I'm sorry, baby.

03:49.062 --> 03:52.032
If you want to go out,
we can go out.

03:55.402 --> 03:57.971
Thank you, baby, oh!

03:58.004 --> 03:59.472
I'll call
Sheila's babysitter

03:59.506 --> 04:01.074
and tell her
she can come tomorrow.

04:01.107 --> 04:02.676
Why do we got to
pay a babysitter

04:02.709 --> 04:04.511
when Chris'll do it for free?

04:04.544 --> 04:06.579
No, he does it during
the day, not at night.

04:06.613 --> 04:08.348
Rochelle, we don't
really need...

04:08.381 --> 04:10.650
Do you want me
to make you some chicken?

04:12.519 --> 04:15.522
Okay, well, I'm gonna
call Sheila's babysitter.

04:16.423 --> 04:18.391
[DOORBELL BUZZES]

04:18.425 --> 04:19.893
Hi, I'm Yvette.

04:19.926 --> 04:21.561
Oh, okay,
come on in.

04:23.530 --> 04:25.498
Okay, so I have
some chicken

04:25.532 --> 04:27.434
baking in the oven.
Just take it out

04:27.467 --> 04:28.702
in about
20 minutes.

04:28.735 --> 04:30.637
Chris and Drew
are gonna watch the game.

04:30.670 --> 04:32.739
What am I gonna do
while Chris and Drew

04:32.772 --> 04:33.973
are watching the game?

04:34.007 --> 04:35.508
Well,
you can hang with me.

04:35.542 --> 04:37.410
I'll show you
how to do French braids.

04:37.444 --> 04:38.678
Okay.
[CHUCKLES]

04:38.712 --> 04:40.880
Yvette, I left the number
to the restaurant

04:40.914 --> 04:42.382
by the phone.

04:42.415 --> 04:44.651
Now, call me if anything
goes wrong, okay?

04:44.684 --> 04:46.386
Everything's
gonna be fine.

04:46.419 --> 04:48.922
Chris, I don't want
that girl calling us.

04:48.955 --> 04:50.657
So if there's
a problem...

04:50.690 --> 04:51.758
handle it.

04:51.791 --> 04:53.626
Me and your mother
don't go out often,

04:53.660 --> 04:55.862
so I don't want
nothing to spoil it.

04:55.895 --> 04:57.364
Here.

04:57.397 --> 05:00.066
Whoa, what's this?
That's emergency money.

05:00.100 --> 05:03.503
NARRATOR:
<i>My father believed there's</i>
<i>nothing $10 couldn't fix.</i>

05:03.536 --> 05:04.938
What if something
costs $11?

05:04.971 --> 05:06.106
Talk them down to 10.

05:06.139 --> 05:07.841
Got it.

05:07.874 --> 05:10.577
Okay, you guys be good.
All right, Chris.

05:10.610 --> 05:12.445
Call me if you need
anything, okay?

05:12.479 --> 05:14.014
YVETTE: Okay.
Okay, bye, y'all.

05:14.047 --> 05:15.615
Bye.
Bye-bye.
Bye, Dad.

05:15.648 --> 05:18.418
JULIUS: Bye, sweetie.
Take your time and have fun.

05:24.624 --> 05:26.426
Welcome to Pastures
and Shores.

05:26.459 --> 05:27.660
May I take your order?

05:28.862 --> 05:31.097
Okay, I'll have
the all-you-can-eat

05:31.131 --> 05:33.433
shrimp and sirloin combo,
well done,

05:33.466 --> 05:35.435
order of coleslaw
and a Coke.

05:35.468 --> 05:36.836
And you, sir?
JULIUS: I'll have

05:36.870 --> 05:40.140
the ultimate surf and turf
and a large Coke.

05:41.474 --> 05:42.842
[CASHIER TYPING]

05:42.876 --> 05:45.011
[REGISTER DINGS]
That'll be 17.99.

05:45.045 --> 05:47.614
Ooh. Wait, baby.

05:47.647 --> 05:49.416
Are you sure
we can afford this?

05:49.449 --> 05:52.052
It's okay.
I have coupons.

05:52.085 --> 05:55.555
NARRATOR:
<i>If there was a coupon for</i>
<i>something, my father had it.</i>

05:55.588 --> 05:57.557
Whoa, whoa,
whoa!

05:57.590 --> 05:59.092
What's this?

05:59.125 --> 06:01.795
A coupon--
No tickets on Tuesday.

06:02.896 --> 06:05.532
This doesn't include
the all-you-can-eat

06:05.565 --> 06:06.866
shrimp and sirloin combo.

06:06.900 --> 06:08.468
Oh, you know what?

06:08.501 --> 06:09.803
I'll just order
something else.

06:09.836 --> 06:11.471
I'll take the--
No, it's okay.

06:11.504 --> 06:13.006
I want everything
to be perfect.

06:13.039 --> 06:14.808
Get what you want.

06:14.841 --> 06:16.543
I'll pay for it.

06:24.050 --> 06:25.485
Is there a problem?

06:25.518 --> 06:27.554
Can I have my coupon?

06:27.587 --> 06:30.824
ANNOUNCER [ON TV]:
<i>...to Irving inside,</i>
<i>and Irving gets the basket.</i>

06:30.857 --> 06:33.493
NARRATOR:
<i>Having a babysitter</i>
<i>in the house was great,</i>

06:33.526 --> 06:36.496
<i>because the only kid</i>
<i>I had to worry about was me.</i>

06:36.529 --> 06:38.631
[PHONE RINGS]

06:40.867 --> 06:42.469
I'll be right back.

06:42.502 --> 06:44.137
ANNOUNCER:
<i>Sixers beat the Knicks</i>
<i>five out of six.</i>

06:44.170 --> 06:45.905
No, I can't talk right now.

06:45.939 --> 06:47.907
NARRATOR:
<i>My mother would never hire</i>
<i>someone</i>

06:47.941 --> 06:49.609
<i>she thought was irresponsible.</i>

06:49.642 --> 06:51.211
<i>But irresponsible people</i>
<i>never tell you</i>

06:51.244 --> 06:54.681
<i>that they're irresponsible--</i>
<i>because they're irresponsible!</i>

06:57.550 --> 06:58.918
Chris, I gotta go.

06:58.952 --> 07:01.254
What do you mean, you gotta go?
I got something

07:01.287 --> 07:02.922
I gotta do.
You are doing something!

07:02.956 --> 07:05.725
You stayed with your brother
and sister before, right?

07:05.759 --> 07:07.660
Yeah, but that's only
during the day.

07:07.694 --> 07:10.530
You'll be fine.
I'll be right back.

07:10.563 --> 07:14.801
NARRATOR:
<i>At that moment, I wanted to</i>
<i>bust her right upside the head.</i>

07:14.834 --> 07:16.236
I'm hungry.

07:17.604 --> 07:20.173
ROCHELLE:
Oh, our food, yeah.

07:20.206 --> 07:21.274
Oh.

07:21.307 --> 07:22.676
Thank you.

07:22.709 --> 07:24.077
JULIUS:
I am hungry.

07:24.110 --> 07:25.512
Thank you.

07:25.545 --> 07:27.647
Oh, wait, wait.
Uh, excuse me.

07:27.681 --> 07:29.783
I ordered coleslaw,
but this is potato salad.

07:29.816 --> 07:30.917
I'll get the manager.

07:30.950 --> 07:32.652
We don't want
the manager.

07:32.686 --> 07:33.953
We want coleslaw.

07:33.987 --> 07:36.022
I'll get the manager.

07:40.593 --> 07:41.961
Is there a problem?

07:41.995 --> 07:45.632
Uh, my wife ordered coleslaw
and got potato salad.

07:45.665 --> 07:47.100
I'm sorry
for the misunderstanding,

07:47.133 --> 07:49.169
but that meal comes with
potato salad.

07:49.202 --> 07:50.870
But I ordered coleslaw.

07:50.904 --> 07:52.572
But it comes with
potato salad.

07:52.605 --> 07:53.773
We'd be happy
to sell you

07:53.807 --> 07:55.241
a side of coleslaw
for 79 cents,

07:55.275 --> 07:57.243
you just have
to get back in line.

07:57.277 --> 08:00.246
NARRATOR:
<i>Never go out on the day</i>
<i>they give out welfare checks.</i>

08:00.280 --> 08:03.016
You got a thousand paper cups
of coleslaw back there.

08:03.049 --> 08:05.151
You can't take this back
and bring her one?

08:05.185 --> 08:07.587
Know what? Never mind.
Just bring me a bowl--

08:07.620 --> 08:09.756
I'll have some of his
coleslaw. Not a problem.

08:09.789 --> 08:11.191
No, no,
can't do that, ma'am.

08:11.224 --> 08:12.792
We have a no-sharing policy.

08:14.361 --> 08:15.729
So what
you're telling me

08:15.762 --> 08:16.863
is that I can't have

08:16.896 --> 08:18.264
some of my husband's
coleslaw?

08:18.298 --> 08:20.033
That's what you're
saying to me?

08:20.066 --> 08:23.003
[LAUGHS]
You could, but we would
have to ask you to leave.

08:23.036 --> 08:25.638
Heh. You know...
You know what?

08:25.672 --> 08:26.906
You know what?
I eat at home.

08:26.940 --> 08:28.608
That's why I cook
my own meals.

08:28.641 --> 08:29.642
I'll get you
coleslaw.

08:29.676 --> 08:31.111
Is there anything else?

08:31.144 --> 08:32.612
Enjoy your meal.

08:32.645 --> 08:34.581
What the hell--
Does he think he's Mr. T?

08:34.614 --> 08:36.282
Why is he acting like that?
It's okay.

08:36.316 --> 08:38.151
This is our night,
it's our night.

08:38.184 --> 08:39.853
You're right.

08:39.886 --> 08:40.854
Oh, man.

08:42.222 --> 08:43.189
What's that?

08:43.223 --> 08:44.324
It's my baby.

08:44.357 --> 08:46.092
You can't bring
that baby here.

08:46.126 --> 08:48.661
Would you be quiet,
and let me handle this?

08:48.695 --> 08:50.030
You can't bring
that baby here.

08:50.063 --> 08:51.798
It'll just be
for a little while.

08:51.831 --> 08:54.167
Did you bring something back
to eat? I'm hungry.

08:54.200 --> 08:58.138
I forgot your mother put some
chicken in the oven for you.

09:02.075 --> 09:04.778
I'm gonna run and get you guys
something to eat.

09:04.811 --> 09:05.879
Watch the baby, okay?

09:05.912 --> 09:07.213
You can't leave
your baby here.

09:07.247 --> 09:09.149
Why not?
Because you're
babysitting.

09:09.182 --> 09:11.651
I'm just going down
to Lincoln Fried Chicken.

09:11.685 --> 09:13.319
What if he gets hungry?
Or throws up?

09:13.353 --> 09:14.688
He won't-- It'll be fine.

09:14.721 --> 09:16.022
I'll be right back.

09:16.056 --> 09:17.791
NARRATOR:
<i>At that moment, I was sure</i>

09:17.824 --> 09:19.793
<i>of two things:</i>
<i> I wasn't gonna be fine,</i>

09:19.826 --> 09:21.861
<i>and she wasn't gonna be</i>
<i>right back.</i>

09:21.895 --> 09:25.265
<i>* Everybody hates Chris </i>

09:25.298 --> 09:27.367
[BABY GURGLING]

09:32.772 --> 09:34.874
[***]

09:36.042 --> 09:37.043
What's this?

09:37.077 --> 09:39.979
Why didn't they just
give you a cup of coleslaw?

09:40.013 --> 09:41.047
It's this big.

09:41.081 --> 09:42.982
It'll be here
in a few minutes.

09:43.016 --> 09:44.284
[SIGHS]

09:44.317 --> 09:45.919
Where you going?
I'm going to check

09:45.952 --> 09:48.288
on the kids.
The kids are fine...

09:48.321 --> 09:49.956
I'm just going to check, okay?

10:00.200 --> 10:03.036
DREW:
Whoa-- A behind the back,
off the backboard dunk!

10:03.069 --> 10:04.871
Chris, man,
you're missing it!

10:04.904 --> 10:05.739
Come on!

10:05.772 --> 10:07.073
Shh, would you be quiet?

10:07.107 --> 10:09.142
Stop yelling
and turn the TV down.

10:09.175 --> 10:11.344
You think she's coming back?
She better.

10:11.378 --> 10:13.713
[PHONE RINGING]

10:22.722 --> 10:23.823
Hello.

10:23.857 --> 10:25.892
Hey, baby, how's it going?

10:25.925 --> 10:27.060
CHRIS:
<i>Good.</i>

10:27.093 --> 10:28.361
<i>[BABY COOING]</i>

10:28.395 --> 10:29.729
Is that a baby?

10:29.763 --> 10:31.831
No, it's the TV.
[CONTINUES COOING]

10:31.865 --> 10:33.233
Oh. Well, where's Yvette?

10:33.266 --> 10:34.968
She's in the bathroom.

10:35.001 --> 10:37.404
Okay. We'll be home
in a little while, all right?

10:37.437 --> 10:38.838
Okay.

10:38.872 --> 10:40.140
<i>Okay, love you.</i>
All right, bye.

10:40.173 --> 10:42.075
NARRATOR:
<i>I know you're thinking:</i>

10:42.108 --> 10:44.411
<i>"Why didn't I just tell</i>
<i>my mother what was going on?"</i>

10:44.444 --> 10:47.714
<i>Well, I figured</i>
<i>it couldn't get any worse.</i>

10:47.747 --> 10:49.115
Hi, um, is Yvette here?

10:49.149 --> 10:51.985
She just left.
And who are you?

10:52.018 --> 10:54.854
I'm Mario.
Is that my baby?

10:56.289 --> 10:57.891
I don't know, is it?

10:57.924 --> 11:00.226
I know.
He takes after his mom.

11:00.260 --> 11:02.996
NARRATOR:
<i>We didn't know</i>
<i>if it was his baby, either.</i>

11:03.029 --> 11:05.832
<i>But trust me, there ain't</i>
<i>no black man picking up a baby</i>

11:05.865 --> 11:08.201
<i>that ain't his.</i>

11:08.234 --> 11:10.470
What's he doing here?
Where did she go?

11:10.503 --> 11:12.138
She went to get us
something to eat.

11:12.172 --> 11:14.841
She's babysitting us.
My boy...

11:14.874 --> 11:16.276
TONYA:
Where you think
you're going?

11:16.309 --> 11:18.511
You can't just leave
with somebody's baby.

11:18.545 --> 11:20.013
Look,
when she comes back,

11:20.046 --> 11:21.948
tell her I'll be over
my mother's house.

11:21.981 --> 11:23.917
DREW:
Whoa! Chris,
you should've seen it!

11:23.950 --> 11:26.152
Bernard King hit a shot
from the top of the key,

11:26.186 --> 11:29.022
stole it and hit another one
right before the half!

11:29.055 --> 11:30.724
I'm hungry.

11:34.527 --> 11:37.497
NARRATOR:
<i>Sometimes my father</i>
<i>would be so focused</i>

11:37.530 --> 11:39.065
<i>on everything going right,</i>

11:39.099 --> 11:40.867
<i>he didn't realize</i>
<i>he was the reason</i>

11:40.900 --> 11:42.168
<i>it was going wrong.</i>

11:42.802 --> 11:44.170
It's okay.

11:44.204 --> 11:47.107
Your coleslaw will be here
any minute.

11:47.140 --> 11:49.509
Why do you make
such a big deal out of nothing?

11:49.542 --> 11:51.444
Because I spent good money
on this.

11:51.478 --> 11:53.046
I expect it to be good.

11:53.079 --> 11:55.448
Well, is it about the money
or is it about me?

11:55.482 --> 11:57.017
Why would you
even ask me that?

11:57.050 --> 11:58.818
We have been waiting
30 minutes

11:58.852 --> 12:00.820
for a Dixie Cup
full of coleslaw.

12:00.854 --> 12:02.088
Think about it.

12:02.822 --> 12:04.224
Never mind.

12:04.257 --> 12:06.092
Oh, finally!

12:12.365 --> 12:14.200
Enjoy your coleslaw.

12:17.837 --> 12:19.239
I'm sorry.

12:19.272 --> 12:21.808
I don't get to take you out
as much as I'd like.

12:21.841 --> 12:23.009
It's okay, baby.

12:23.043 --> 12:25.145
I just want everything
to be right.

12:25.178 --> 12:28.481
But as long as I'm with you,
everything's perfect.

12:28.515 --> 12:30.050
I love you--
[DOORS SWING OPEN]

12:30.083 --> 12:31.051
MAN:
Everybody down!

12:31.084 --> 12:32.385
Get down!
Now!

12:32.419 --> 12:34.187
Damn it!

12:35.889 --> 12:37.590
Hey.
Hey.

12:37.624 --> 12:40.326
NARRATOR:
<i>Isn't it funny how</i>
<i>irresponsible people think</i>

12:40.360 --> 12:42.362
<i>they can change the world</i>
<i>with chicken?</i>

12:42.395 --> 12:44.864
Chris, man, this is the
best game I ever seen.

12:44.898 --> 12:45.965
You gotta come watch.

12:45.999 --> 12:47.300
Chris,
where's the baby?

12:47.334 --> 12:49.102
His father took him.

12:49.135 --> 12:50.837
You gave my baby
to a stranger?

12:50.870 --> 12:52.339
No, to his father.

12:52.372 --> 12:53.840
That could be anybody.

12:54.641 --> 12:56.076
He asked for you
at the door.

12:56.109 --> 12:57.544
And the baby said
"Da-Da."

12:57.577 --> 12:58.611
Who else could it be?

12:58.645 --> 12:59.612
I don't know!

12:59.646 --> 13:00.613
Where'd they go?

13:00.647 --> 13:02.148
To his mother's house.

13:03.650 --> 13:05.985
I know--
You'll be right back.

13:06.019 --> 13:08.188
[ANNOUNCER SPEAKING
INDISTINCTLY ON TV]

13:08.221 --> 13:10.190
Whoo! Yeah!

13:10.223 --> 13:12.225
NARRATOR:
<i>As bad as things were going,</i>

13:12.258 --> 13:14.961
<i>I could always count on</i>
<i>one person to make things go</i>

13:14.994 --> 13:16.596
<i>from bad to worse.</i>

13:16.629 --> 13:18.932
[PHONE RINGING]

13:20.133 --> 13:21.167
Hello?

13:21.201 --> 13:22.902
Hello? I'm looking
for my parents.

13:22.936 --> 13:24.537
They're having dinner
there tonight.

13:24.571 --> 13:26.139
I think you got
the wrong number.

13:26.172 --> 13:27.507
<i>This ain't no restaurant.</i>

13:27.540 --> 13:28.875
Tonya,
what are you doing?

13:28.908 --> 13:30.143
Hey! What are you doing?

13:30.176 --> 13:32.245
I'm calling Mom.
I'm answering the phone!

13:32.278 --> 13:34.147
Are you trying
to mess everything up?

13:34.180 --> 13:36.416
You gonna mess everything up.
Just put the money in there!

13:36.449 --> 13:38.318
Mom said call
if anything went wrong.

13:38.351 --> 13:40.920
Something went wrong,
so I'm calling.

13:40.954 --> 13:43.089
Tonya, no.
They're on a date.

13:43.123 --> 13:45.225
If you call, you're
gonna mess everything up.

13:45.258 --> 13:48.028
Then Mama will be mad at Dad,
Dad will be mad at me.

13:48.061 --> 13:49.929
Just let me
handle this, okay?

13:49.963 --> 13:51.231
All I know is

13:51.264 --> 13:53.867
somebody better
French braid my hair.

13:56.136 --> 13:57.337
Give me the money,
big man!

13:57.370 --> 13:59.239
Just watch where
you point that thing.

13:59.272 --> 14:01.174
ROBBER 1:
Don't tell me
where to watch.

14:01.207 --> 14:03.143
I'll point this
wherever I want.

14:03.176 --> 14:05.111
Julius,
just be quiet.

14:05.145 --> 14:06.913
You better listen
to your girl.

14:06.946 --> 14:08.648
Hey, that's not my girl,
that's my wife.

14:08.682 --> 14:10.083
ROBBER 2:
Hey, man, come on,

14:10.116 --> 14:11.618
just get the money
and let's go.

14:11.651 --> 14:13.386
No, man over here
trying to be a hero.

14:13.420 --> 14:14.921
ROBBER 2:
Hey, come on,
I got this.

14:14.954 --> 14:16.122
I got this.

14:17.691 --> 14:18.658
Chelle?

14:18.692 --> 14:19.959
Huh?

14:19.993 --> 14:21.161
Is that you?

14:21.961 --> 14:23.663
It's me, Ricky!

14:23.697 --> 14:25.365
Remember? From Flatbush!

14:25.398 --> 14:29.069
I'm sorry, I-I don't believe
I know who you are.

14:29.102 --> 14:30.470
I used to be at the club

14:30.503 --> 14:32.038
with Shine and them,
remember?

14:32.072 --> 14:33.406
We used to pop lock.

14:35.342 --> 14:36.976
[GRUNTS]

14:38.011 --> 14:39.045
Remember?

14:39.079 --> 14:40.947
[GASPS]
Ricky Edwards?

14:40.980 --> 14:42.148
Donna's brother!

14:42.182 --> 14:44.117
Yeah! Yeah!
How you been?

14:44.150 --> 14:47.354
Oh, good till now.
How you been?

14:47.387 --> 14:48.555
Oh, I'm hanging in there.

14:48.588 --> 14:49.723
All right.

14:49.756 --> 14:51.624
Hey, since you all
so tight,

14:51.658 --> 14:53.226
why don't you
just let us slide?

14:53.259 --> 14:56.396
Hey, man, if it was up to me,
I would.

14:56.429 --> 14:58.631
But my partner...crazy.

14:58.665 --> 15:01.401
So you all going to have
to put something in the bag.

15:01.434 --> 15:04.037
Why don't we pretend
we put something in the bag?

15:04.070 --> 15:05.205
Because this ain't
no pretend robbery!

15:05.238 --> 15:07.640
Julius, just give him
the money.

15:07.674 --> 15:10.610
Um, can you just leave us
a little for the babysitter?

15:10.643 --> 15:11.644
You know how it is.

15:11.678 --> 15:13.380
You got kids?

15:13.413 --> 15:14.948
Boy, I got three!

15:15.648 --> 15:18.451
Two boys
and a girl!

15:18.485 --> 15:19.986
Kids, they a blessing.

15:20.020 --> 15:21.121
Yeah,
love of my life.

15:21.154 --> 15:22.322
Dig. Look,
just give me 20.

15:22.355 --> 15:24.090
Hurry up
before my man see you.

15:24.124 --> 15:26.693
Give him, give him!
Hurry, before my partner sees.

15:29.029 --> 15:30.764
Chelle...
It was good seeing you, girl.

15:30.797 --> 15:32.198
Aw, you too, man.

15:32.232 --> 15:34.668
Hey!
Don't tell nobody I did this.

15:34.701 --> 15:37.037
[***]

15:39.239 --> 15:40.507
Hello.
TONYA: Hi.

15:40.540 --> 15:41.508
Is Yvette here?

15:41.541 --> 15:42.542
Who are you?

15:42.575 --> 15:44.010
I'm her mother.

15:44.044 --> 15:45.278
I came to pick up
the baby.

15:45.311 --> 15:47.614
His father took him.
Where's Yvette?

15:47.647 --> 15:49.149
She said
she'll be right back.

15:49.182 --> 15:52.018
Then again, she said that
30 minutes ago.

15:52.052 --> 15:54.421
You mind if I come in
and wait for her?

15:54.454 --> 15:56.389
Come in.

16:02.128 --> 16:03.563
Is everybody okay?

16:03.596 --> 16:05.432
No, we're not okay, man,

16:05.465 --> 16:07.434
we just got robbed.
Julius...

16:07.467 --> 16:09.402
NARRATOR:
<i>After everything that happened,</i>

16:09.436 --> 16:11.604
<i>you would expect</i>
<i>my mother's reaction</i>

16:11.638 --> 16:13.273
<i>to be a little like this...</i>

16:13.306 --> 16:16.042
You are such a brave man.

16:16.076 --> 16:18.545
Oh, baby, thank you
for taking me to dinner

16:18.578 --> 16:21.047
and standing up
to those robbers.

16:21.081 --> 16:22.816
Oh, baby,
I love you so much.

16:22.849 --> 16:25.752
NARRATOR:
<i>Instead, it went</i>
<i>a little something like this.</i>

16:25.785 --> 16:28.254
Are you crazy?

16:28.288 --> 16:30.790
What was you thinking, arguing
with a masked gunman?

16:30.824 --> 16:32.625
You could have
been killed!

16:32.659 --> 16:33.827
Do you think
I got married

16:33.860 --> 16:35.495
to raise three kids
by myself?

16:35.528 --> 16:38.465
The next time somebody
tries to rob us...

16:38.498 --> 16:40.600
get robbed!

16:40.633 --> 16:42.302
Let's go!

16:44.771 --> 16:47.173
Here's a coupon for
a free meal

16:47.207 --> 16:49.075
if you decide
to come back again.

16:49.109 --> 16:51.211
Thanks, man.
Julius!

16:51.244 --> 16:53.380
Take two.
Good luck.

16:56.449 --> 16:59.586
[BASKETBALL GAME PLAYING
INDISTINCTLY ON TV]

17:02.222 --> 17:03.456
What happened to
your hair?

17:03.490 --> 17:05.225
Yvette said she was
gonna teach me

17:05.258 --> 17:06.659
how to French braid.

17:06.693 --> 17:08.395
Does Yvette live with you?

17:08.428 --> 17:09.362
Yes. Why?

17:09.396 --> 17:11.197
My mama said
if I have a baby

17:11.231 --> 17:12.665
before I get married,

17:12.699 --> 17:14.134
she says
she's putting me out

17:14.167 --> 17:15.802
because she ain't raising
no babies.

17:15.835 --> 17:18.238
You like raising babies?
No.

17:18.271 --> 17:20.106
How come you
didn't put her out?

17:20.140 --> 17:21.675
How old are you?

17:21.708 --> 17:23.276
Nine.

17:23.309 --> 17:25.111
[DOORBELL BUZZES]

17:25.145 --> 17:26.813
I'll get it!

17:28.248 --> 17:29.549
You mother's here.

17:33.386 --> 17:35.355
Chris, this is the best game
I ever seen!

17:35.388 --> 17:36.389
You gotta come watch!

17:39.759 --> 17:41.695
How come you didn't tell me
you were babysitting?

17:41.728 --> 17:43.296
Why are you in my business?

17:43.329 --> 17:45.699
You live in my house,
you don't have any business.

17:45.732 --> 17:47.367
I don't have
to live at your house.

17:47.400 --> 17:48.635
I'll move in
with Mario.

17:48.668 --> 17:50.136
You think
Mario's mother

17:50.170 --> 17:51.838
wants to deal with you?
You need a job.

17:51.871 --> 17:53.606
Why do you think
I'm babysitting?

17:53.640 --> 17:54.674
You weren't even here.

17:54.708 --> 17:55.909
I was coming right back.

17:55.942 --> 17:57.544
Hey, hey!
That's enough.

17:57.577 --> 17:59.546
Excuse me?
CHRIS: You gotta leave,

17:59.579 --> 18:01.614
and take that baby with you.
Fine!

18:01.648 --> 18:03.149
Not you, her.

18:03.183 --> 18:04.884
I don't know if that's
such a good idea.

18:04.918 --> 18:06.419
CHRIS:
If my mom comes home

18:06.453 --> 18:07.854
and finds out
what happened,

18:07.887 --> 18:09.823
she's gonna ask me
why I didn't tell her.

18:09.856 --> 18:11.157
And I'm gonna say

18:11.191 --> 18:12.559
because my dad
told me not to.

18:12.592 --> 18:14.894
And then she's gonna
curse him out and kill me.

18:14.928 --> 18:16.296
[SIGHS]

18:16.329 --> 18:17.564
When are you
coming home?

18:17.597 --> 18:20.567
As soon as his
mom and dad come back.

18:20.600 --> 18:22.569
[BABY COOING]

18:26.239 --> 18:27.474
Are you still
gonna teach me

18:27.507 --> 18:28.875
how to French braid
my hair?

18:28.908 --> 18:30.410
Yeah. Heh.

18:30.443 --> 18:32.612
Oh, Chris, why don't you
go watch your game?

18:32.645 --> 18:35.448
Three, two, one!

18:35.482 --> 18:36.583
Oh, man!

18:36.616 --> 18:40.320
That was a good game!
Heh, heh.

18:40.353 --> 18:41.521
[CHANGES CHANNEL]

18:41.554 --> 18:42.889
WOMAN 1 [ON TV]:
<i>What are you doing here?</i>

18:42.922 --> 18:44.491
WOMAN 2 [ON TV]:
<i>I came for the makeover!</i>

18:44.524 --> 18:46.393
Everything went okay?
Everything went so good.

18:46.426 --> 18:47.594
We had so much fun.

18:47.627 --> 18:49.262
ROCHELLE: Good!
YVETTE: They were good.

18:49.295 --> 18:50.330
We should do it
again.

18:50.363 --> 18:51.531
ROCHELLE:
For sure!

18:51.564 --> 18:53.667
Maybe we could go
to a movie next time.

18:53.700 --> 18:56.569
NARRATOR:
<i>I wanted this to be</i>
<i>a good night for my parents.</i>

18:56.603 --> 18:59.806
<i>and I didn't want my father to</i>
<i>think I couldn't handle things.</i>

18:59.839 --> 19:02.842
<i>So I decided to keep</i>
<i>everything that happened...</i>

19:02.876 --> 19:04.411
<i>to myself.</i>

19:04.444 --> 19:06.646
JULIUS:
Yvette,
are you free next Friday?

19:06.680 --> 19:07.881
No, no, no, no, no!

19:07.914 --> 19:09.382
She left us to go get a baby.

19:09.416 --> 19:11.451
When she came back,
she burnt your chicken.

19:11.484 --> 19:13.486
Then, this guy came
to the door asking for the baby.

19:13.520 --> 19:15.622
His name was Mario
and was the baby's father.

19:15.655 --> 19:17.323
When he left,
she came back,

19:17.357 --> 19:18.491
and the baby wasn't here.

19:18.525 --> 19:20.427
She went
to get the baby back,

19:20.460 --> 19:22.328
her mother came to the door
looking for her and the baby.

19:22.362 --> 19:23.863
They had a fight
about where to live.

19:23.897 --> 19:26.633
She said she'd live at Mario's
house. Who is Mario?

19:26.666 --> 19:28.435
When she came back,
she braided Tonya's hair.

19:28.468 --> 19:30.270
Drew got to watch the game,
you guys came back.

19:30.303 --> 19:32.372
She's trying to make it look
like everything

19:32.405 --> 19:34.374
was all peachy and fine.
It's not!

19:34.407 --> 19:36.776
[***]

19:36.810 --> 19:40.447
I told you we should have
let Chris babysit.

19:40.480 --> 19:42.248
Girl, give me
my money back.

19:42.282 --> 19:44.284
I'mma kick her ass.

19:44.317 --> 19:45.919
Hold my wig.
[BELL RINGS]

19:45.952 --> 19:51.524
<i>* Everybody hates Chris </i>

19:51.558 --> 19:54.661
NARRATOR:
<i>Stay tuned for scenes</i>
<i>from our next episode.</i>

19:56.963 --> 19:59.265
[***]

20:00.533 --> 20:02.969
<i>* Aww, make it funky now </i>
